channel.title: Rspsdesign
channel.description:
[center]Hello everyone,
I'm Josh a web developer currently working on a project for players to advertise there servers and download templates.
Anyway here's the site: [url=http://www.rspsdesign.com]www.rspsdesign.com[/url]
Update: Currently working on a log in and log out session via mysql ;)
[/center]

item.title: Rspsdesign
item.dc:creator: @haviland4 haviland4
item.description:
@haviland4 wrote:

[quote=“Ruby, post:19, topic:554805”][quote author=Justin Bieber link=topic=673728.msg4506963#msg4506963 date=1460498142]
don’t listen to these dweebs josh the name is fine mate
[/quote]

Looking outside of the point that it’s ridiculously similar to what Cory’s site was called, why just limit yourself to RSPS designs? The name itself shuns growth into other areas before it’s even on the table[/quote]

yeah I know what you mean I’ve kinda already bought this domain but this isn’t an issue really what I’ll do is finish designing the pages and layout and then transfer the the website to a new domain,

I shouldn’t of really put it onto the table with this name as like you said the name itself shuns growth into other areas

I’ve been working on some more of the website anyway here: http://www.rspsdesign.com/
